h1 Alerts

p Alerts are used to provide feedback to a user based on the urgency of the message that should be displayed. The recommended markup is provided but depending on the context the markup can be switched out as long as the correct classes are used.

h2 Usage

dl.styleguide-usage
  dt Wrapper
  dd To set up an alert create an element to wrap the items that will go inside the alert module and give is a class #{inline_code(".alert-message")}, #{inline_code(".alert-warning")}, #{inline_code(".alert-error")}, or #{inline_code(".alert-success")}. These classes will determine the correct icon and colors to use.
  dt Title
  dd The title bar of the alert is set with the class #{inline_code(".alert-title")}. The text for the title should be short and concise enough to fit on a single line.
  dt Content
  dd The content container is set with the class #{inline_code(".alert-content")} and is meant to be a wrapper. Any type of HTML elements can be placed inside the container including paragraphs, lists, and labels.
  dt Remove Control
  dd Optionally an extra control can be included on an alert that will remove it from the page when clicked. It requires the JavaScript module #{inline_code("jquery.cardinal.alert.js")}.


